        (87227, 'Stella Arroyave', NULL, 'From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia.  Stella Arroyave, Lady Hopkins (born 1956, Colombia) is an actress and producer. She married Sir Anthony Hopkins at a private ceremony in Malibu, California on 1 March 2003. Before her recent move into film Lady Hopkins was an antiques dealer. Sir Anthony explained that he met her one day when he walked into her shop in Pacific Palisades.  Lady Hopkins had a small role in The Human Stain, a film which was directed by Robert Benton and starred Sir Anthony. She later played Gina in Slipstream, an experimental film both written and directed by Sir Anthony, which she also produced. Sir Anthony indicated that Lady Hopkins was a motivating force in the film''s fruition.  Description above from the Wikipedia article Stella Arroyave, licensed under CC-BY-SA, full list of contributors on Wikipedia.   ', 'Colombia', 2, '/3QmiVxWg6G0uJYqbAJKCN51wfAl.jpg'),
