one episode of I Love Lucy as Helen Erickson Kaiser, the childhood friend of Lucy

Ricardo. She also made five guest appearances on Perry Mason during the series''

nine-year run on CBS. In her first appearance in 1959 she played co-defendant

Agnes Nulty in The Case of the Borrowed Brunette. In 1962 she played murderer

Elizabeth Dow in The Case of the Mystified Miner.

During World War II she worked often for the USO, continuing

that service until the war ended in 1945. There she met her husband Jairus

Bellamy. She is credited with seventy-five films in her career, of which

seventeen were westerns, for which she is best known. Bromley retired from

films and lived in the Greater Los Angeles Area until her death in 2003, aged

91.', 'San Francisco - California - USA', 1, '/ezVIMObrxUIImS7awcXu0oNKrrq.jpg'),
